<div class="brand">📚 ENGLISH CODING · 영어코딩</div>
<h1>🔴 M002 Week 6 — Redstone &amp; Levers</h1>
<p><strong>Topic:</strong> Redstone Levers · <strong>Course:</strong> Maze Madness · <strong>Level:</strong> Intermediate · <strong>Time:</strong> about 35 minutes</p>
<p>The maze has a <strong>lever</strong>. Flip it with <code>interact</code> to open the redstone door, then walk to the goal.</p>
<hr />
<h2>1 · Predict 🔮</h2>
<p>Write what the agent does.</p>
<pre><code>move forward
interact ahead
move forward
</code></pre>
<p><strong>The agent flips the lever. What happens to the door?</strong></p>
<p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p>

<pre><code>interact ahead
move forward
move forward
</code></pre>
<p><strong>There is no lever in front. What happens?</strong></p>
<p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p>

<hr />
<h2>2 · Plain to API 🔁</h2>
<p>Match the plain words to the real code line.</p>
<table>
<thead>
<tr>
<th>Plain words</th>
<th>Code</th>
</tr>
</thead>
<tbody>
<tr>
<td>flip the lever in front</td>
<td><code>agent.move(FORWARD, 1)</code></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>step forward one block</td>
<td><code>agent.interact(...)</code></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>is there redstone ahead?</td>
<td><code>agent.detect(REDSTONE, FORWARD)</code></td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
<p><strong>Write each pair:</strong></p>
<p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p>

<hr />
<h2>3 · Trace the Code 🔍</h2>
<pre><code class="language-python">while not agent.detect(REDSTONE, FORWARD):
    agent.move(FORWARD, 1)
agent.interact(...)
agent.move(FORWARD, 1)
agent.move(FORWARD, 1)
</code></pre>
<p><strong>What does the agent do? Write it in plain English.</strong></p>
<p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p>

<hr />
<h2>4 · Fix the Bug 🐛</h2>
<p>The agent should walk <strong>up to</strong> the lever, then flip it <strong>once</strong>. This flips on every step.</p>
<pre><code class="language-python">while not agent.detect(REDSTONE, FORWARD):
    agent.move(FORWARD, 1)
    agent.interact(...)
</code></pre>
<p><strong>Write the fixed code:</strong></p>
<p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p>

<p><strong>One line: why was it wrong?</strong></p>
<p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p>

<hr />
<h2>5 · Show Your Work 📸🎥</h2>
<p>Open your homework world. Write code that:</p>
<ol>
<li>moves the agent to the lever,</li>
<li>flips it with <code>interact</code>,</li>
<li>walks through the open door to the goal.</li>
</ol>
<p>Record <strong>one video</strong> (a phone is fine). Show two things:</p>
<p><strong>1 · Your code.</strong> Scroll through it. Say what each part does.</p>
<p><strong>2 · Your build.</strong> Point the camera. Name the parts.</p>
<p>Fill the blanks:</p>
<blockquote>
<p>Today I built ______.</p>
<p>I built it using this code: ______.</p>
<p>In this code I used ______.</p>
<p>The hardest part was ______.</p>
<p>That part was hard because ______.</p>
</blockquote>
<p><strong>Write your lines here, then say them in your video.</strong></p>
<p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p>

